    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute><dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 31. 1787.</dateline></opener>
                <p>That many happy returns of this season may attend miss Bulls<note type="editorial"><persName ref="pe0331">Elizabeth</persName> and <persName ref="pe0336">Catherine Bull</persName>.</note>
                &amp; y<del><gap unit="letters" quantity="2" reason="illegible"/>g</del>ourself is the sincere wish of y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    forgotten friend. I inclose the drawings you desired: &amp; now shall become master of <persName ref="pe0014">moses</persName>
                    again. his first labors will be to illuminate the copy of the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0025">Introduction to the arctic Zoology</title></bibl>
                    of which several sheets are printed. The objects will not be very numerous chiefly headlands. If you wish a set 
                    <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="2" reason="illegible"/></del> it shall be done at the same time with my own. But let me 
                    recommend to you to get a good impression of the Prints of the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0621">pyrated edition of <persName ref="pe0045">Cook</persName>'s voy by <persName ref="pe0857">Fielding</persName></title></bibl>.
                    They are beautifully done &amp; will fit exactly the lower margin.</p>
                <p>Excepted my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0039">London</title></bibl>, all my future writing will be for private amusement. I grow old 
                    &amp; cannot support the plague of publication: But my drawings &amp; every good office I can do will ever be at y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    command. Pray let me know if <persName ref="pe0431">Thane</persName> has done anything new. It will be acceptable as I do not visit 
                    <placeName ref="pl0699">Town</placeName> till november.</p>
                <p>In respect to <persName ref="pe0014">Moses</persName> I have payed him. Be so good as to discharge the debt to 
                    <persName ref="pe0329">Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Gosling</persName> &amp; favor me with their receit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am with true regard
                    <lb/>Dear Sir
                    <lb/>most faithfully y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
